Yesterday was the first anniversary of the killing of Gen Soleimani, top spymaster and master tactician in Middle East battlefields.Iran has, by and large, showed diplomatic restraint or “strategic patience” but internal pressure is mounting on Tehran. Two major assassination attacks, which killed top general Qassem Soleimani and a leading nuclear scientist, Dr Fakhrizadeh, besides unspecified damage on its nuclear facility, headlined Iran’s 2020 story.
In fact, yesterday was the first anniversary of the killing of Gen Soleimani, top spymaster and master tactician in Middle East battlefields like Iraq and Syria, whom, interestingly, the United States is said to have worked with to defeat ISIS.



