Iran has, by and large, showed diplomatic restraint or “strategic patience” but internal pressure is mounting on Tehran to avenge the alleged foreign sabotage operations. The reasoning for the “external aggression” is the Persian country being seen as a security threat to Israel. 
With the backing of outgoing US President Donald Trump, Israeli Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu has lately started to form a seemingly widening alliance against Iran under the so-called peace deals with neighbouring Mideast states, such as Bahrain and Qatar, at the expense of the long-standing Palestinian question.



