Security threat
Instructively, historian and former Israel Defence Force (IDF) soldier, Prof Avi Shlaim, has previously pointed out that Iran may be a strategic threat to Israel but not an existential security threat as presented in the global political arena.
Two years ago, Prof Shlaim told Aljazeera’s Head to Head programme, in which former Israel’s deputy foreign minister Danny Ayalon appeared, that, unlike the Jewish state, Iran has never attacked a neighbour, has signed the Non-Proliferation Treaty, submits to International Atomic Energy Agency (IAEA) inspections and has no nuclear weapons yet Israel has a stockpile of 75 to 400 of them.



